blog.description: I'm Becky, I'm 24 and I'm from England, but I live and work in Hanoi, Vietnam. I'm an English teacher in primary schools all over the city.. All about the babe vibes. I really really really like to eat.I'm trying really hard to be kind to myself. I want to run a 10K in Ho Chi Minh City in January - that's my current goal!

summary:

I had a horrible day so my friend...
body:
It’s a little bit cooler here in Hanoi! I enjoyed my run a lot more than the other day.

I had a horrible day so my friend brought over bags of food! We had banh xeo which is big crispy pancakes filled with tiny prawns, pork mince and bean sprouts, and nem lui which are kind of like fresh spring rolls with pork skewers and salad. You dip it all in sweet sauce and it’s bloody AMAZING I have a food baby the size of JUPITER

summary: I’m Tired Of Being Accused Of 'Faking' My Need For A Service Animal
title: I’m Tired Of Being Accused Of 'Faking' My Need For A Service Animal
excerpt: This piece was originally published on Rooted in Rights. By Reid Knight Recently, while on a date, the subject of service animals came up. My...
description:
This article 100% needs to exist and this message needs to get out there, and I’m glad that Huffington Post published it.

Now, I’m going to make an political observation than in no way reflects any ill will against the author, Reid Knight, himself.

I find it interesting that Huffington Post would publish an article about a self “described queer, autistic, and mentally ill disability rights advocate”, being accused of falsely claiming to need service dog, meanwhile news reports about “invisibly disabled” military veterans being unfairly targeted for utilizing service animals in public tend to get carried by Fox News and even further right wing news sources that verge on being alt-right.

This trend is just what I’ve observed over the past six or so years, and I comment on it to say that its unfortunate that news media seems to be picking and choosing which disabled people it considers fashionable to publish support for based on politics.
